sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the Russell 3000 index, there is noteworthy activity today in FedEx Corp (Symbol: FDX), where a total volume of 10,626 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 1.1 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 53.5% of FDX's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 2.0 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $160 strike put option expiring May 24, 2019, with 623 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 62,300 underlying shares of FDX.
